The article is a transcript of a speech given by Vice President Kamala Harris at the White House to celebrate the Las Vegas Aces, winners of the 2022 WNBA championship. Harris thanks everyone involved in supporting the team and congratulates them on their accomplishments. She highlights the team's determination and resilience, as well as the leadership of coach Becky Hammon and player A'ja Wilson. Harris also discusses the issue of equal pay for women athletes and recognizes the Aces' advocacy on this issue. She concludes by encouraging the team to continue to be trailblazers and inspire future generations. The speech is followed by remarks from team president Nikki Fargas, who praises the team's success and their impact as leaders in the community.